!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 6

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GeorgiaPro-CondLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Georgia Pro Cond Light Italic (GeorgiaPro-CondLightItalic.ttf)

name

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 16/17

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Light Italic' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Mac NID 16/17

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Light Italic' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

name

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 6

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GeorgiaPro-CondRegular', Everything looks good.

Georgia Pro Cond Regular (GeorgiaPro-CondRegular.ttf)

name

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 16/17

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond'.

Pass

Georgia Pro Cond Italic (GeorgiaPro-CondItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GeorgiaPro-CondItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Georgia Pro Cond Italic (GeorgiaPro-CondItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 8/13

License text if Manufactur (NID 8) is one of these 'Monotype Imaging Inc.', 'Monotype Imaging Inc', 'Monotype ITC Inc.', 'Monotype Hong Kong Limited', 'Monotype Limited', 'Monotype KK', 'Monotype Solutions India Private Limited'

Please verify against job spec.
MS NID 13 is:
Microsoft supplied font. You may use this font to create, display, and print content as permitted by the license terms or terms of use, of the Microsoft product, service, or content in which this font was included. You may only (i) embed this font in content as permitted by the embedding restrictions included in this font; and (ii) temporarily download this font to a printer or other output device to help print content. Any other use is prohibited.
but should be:
This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Pass

Georgia Pro Cond Italic (GeorgiaPro-CondItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Italic' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Georgia Pro Cond Semibold Regular (GeorgiaPro-CondSemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GeorgiaPro-CondSemibold', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Semibold' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond Semibold'.

Georgia Pro Cond Semibold Italic (GeorgiaPro-CondSemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GeorgiaPro-CondSemiboldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Microsoft supplied font. You may use this font to create, display, and print content as permitted by the license terms or terms of use, of the Microsoft product, service, or content in which this font was included. You may only (i) embed this font in content as permitted by the embedding restrictions included in this font; and (ii) temporarily download this font to a printer or other output device to help print content. Any other use is prohibited.

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Georgia Pro Cond Semibold Italic (GeorgiaPro-CondSemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Semibold Italic' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond Semibold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Microsoft supplied font. You may use this font to create, display, and print content as permitted by the license terms or terms of use, of the Microsoft product, service, or content in which this font was included. You may only (i) embed this font in content as permitted by the embedding restrictions included in this font; and (ii) temporarily download this font to a printer or other output device to help print content. Any other use is prohibited.

You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Georgia Pro Cond Bold (GeorgiaPro-CondBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GeorgiaPro-CondBold', Everything looks good.

Georgia Pro Cond Bold (GeorgiaPro-CondBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Bold' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Bold'.

Pass

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 16/17

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Bold Italic' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Bold Italic'.

Georgia Pro Cond Bold Italic (GeorgiaPro-CondBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Bold Italic' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Bold Italic'.

Any other use is prohibited.[ ]'

Warning

Georgia Pro Cond Black Regular (GeorgiaPro-CondBlack.ttf)

name

NID 13 (0, 3, 0, 13)

'License Description' has invalid entry.

Name table entry contains line break, but shouldn't:
'Microsoft supplied font. You may use this font to create, display, and print content as permitted by the license terms or terms of use, of the Microsoft product, service, or content in which this font was included. You may only (i) embed this font in content as permitted by the embedding restrictions included in this font; and (ii) temporarily download this font to a printer or other output device to help print content. Any other use is prohibited.[ ]'

Info

Georgia Pro Cond Black Regular (GeorgiaPro-CondBlack.ttf)

name

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 8/13

License text.

There is a license text but no manufactur. Please verify agains spec.
The license text is:
Microsoft supplied font. You may use this font to create, display, and print content as permitted by the license terms or terms of use, of the Microsoft product, service, or content in which this font was included. You may only (i) embed this font in content as permitted by the embedding restrictions included in this font; and (ii) temporarily download this font to a printer or other output device to help print content. Any other use is prohibited.

Pass

Georgia Pro Cond Black Regular (GeorgiaPro-CondBlack.ttf)

name

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 16/17

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Georgia Pro' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Cond Black' = NID 1 'Georgia Pro Cond Black'.

Pass

NID 6 is 'GeorgiaPro-CondBlack', Everything looks good.
